      <hedline>
        <hl1>Offensive Language</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Louisiana State University Prof Joseph V Ricapito letter opposes Matthew Gurewitsch's use of term 'spaghetti-tenor' in his May 28 article on great Italian tenors (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I was appalled and offended at Matthew Gurewitsch's use of the term ''spaghetti-tenor'' in his article ''Make Room on Olympus for Today's Sacred Monsters'' [May 28]. Does he think that Caruso and Martinelli, Pavarotti and many, many other great Italian tenors deserve this identification? Would you refer to Jussi Bjoerling as a lutefisk tenor?</p>
        <p>JOSEPH V. RICAPITO  Baton Rouge, La.</p>
        <p>The writer is a professor of Italian studies at Louisiana State University.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
